The paper deals with combinatorial structures and their extensions, which are typical topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The examples given in the abstract, such as finite linear orders and permutations, are also common topics in combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions automata, which are a fundamental concept in theoretical computer science (cs.FL). The study of prolificity in combinatorial structures involves analyzing their structural properties, which can be related to graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the classification of unique minimal prolific compositions, which can be seen as a problem in computational complexity (cs.CC) or graph theory (cs.GT).
